The paper deals with privacy-preserving statistical analysis on distributed databases, which is a topic that falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of random sampling and analysis of estimation error also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of encryption and differential privacy suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
